<div align='center'><font size='4'><b>GRAND OPENING WEEKEND!</b></font><br>
<img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/news_elec_store_1_v1.gif' border='1'>
</div>
<br>
<b>Thursday, February 23, 2006</b> &mdash; All of Millsberry is gearing up for the new <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=12">Home Entertainment Superstore</a>'s opening in <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/main_map.phtml?location=downtown">Downtown Millsberry</a>!  The store's owner, Angela Winter, is putting the finishing touches on the store's inventory and preparing her staff for the very special grand opening.  The "Early Bird Breakfast Bonanza," as Winter calls it, will begin at 8 a.m. PST on Friday, February 24th and be held from 8 to 10 a.m. on Saturday the 25th and Sunday the 26th as well.<br> <br>"We've got the breakfast food all ready to go for everyone who comes in to browse, and stacks of free t-shirts are waiting to be handed out to anyone who makes a purchase between 8 and 10 a.m.," Winter told the <i>Gazette</i>.  "We're all really looking forward to the Breakfast Bonanza sale this weekend!"<br> <br>Miss Winter also said she's planning a special customer Rewards Program, which will allow loyal customers to purchase exclusive collectible gadgets not available to the general public.  "Community support is so important to the success of a new store," said Winter, "which is why I want to reward our most loyal customers.  Keep in mind, though, that making a purchase isn't required to join the Rewards Program! Anyone who has a sincere interest in technology will be invited to join."<br> <br>Excitement is building among Millsberry's technology enthusiasts.  "This store is going to be SO awesome!" said Eric Chapman, of Metro Park.  "I can't wait to go in and have a look at all the cool new merchandise.  I can see myself going by the store every day, just to make sure that I'm aware of all the latest releases as they hit the shelves."  Other potential customers are simply eager to get their home entertainment systems set up.  "My television broke a few weeks ago," said Keeley McGann, of Westridge, "so I've been watching all my favorite shows at my friend's house.  I can't wait to finally buy a brand-new TV!"<br> <br>With the offer of a free breakfast and t-shirts, the grand opening of the home entertainment superstore and the Early Bird Breakfast Bonanza are sure to be great successes.  Don't forget to <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=12">visit</a> Friday through Sunday between 8 and 10 a.m. PST! <br>
